Items.description: Vegas Golden Knights coach Peter DeBoer said Thursday one goal could get a raucous home crowd involved and make the difference in a playoff game.
Items.vs: Vegas Golden Knights vs. Colorado Avalanche

Items.description: Just when it seemed the game might be slipping away, Nikita Kucherov asserted himself for the Tampa Bay Lightning.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Lightning vs. Carolina Hurricanes
New York Islanders vs. Boston Bruins

Items.description: Joel Armia had two goals and an assist, Carey Price made 26 saves, and the Montreal Canadiens defeated the Winnipeg Jets 5-1 on Sunday night to take a 3-0 lead in their second-round playoff series.
Items.vs: Montréal Canadiens vs. Winnipeg Jets

Items.description: After the Vegas Golden Knights lost the first two games of their second-round series against the Colorado Avalanche, captain Mark Stone said no team is out of a series until it loses at home.
Items.vs: Vegas Golden Knights vs. Colorado Avalanche

Items.description: With five minutes left and his New York Islanders bleeding away their three-goal lead, coach Barry Trotz called a timeout and told his players to breathe.
Items.vs: Boston Bruins vs. New York Islanders

Items.description: Tyler Toffoli scored at 1:39 of overtime, lifting the Montreal Canadiens to a 3-2 victory over the Winnipeg Jets on Monday night and a four-game sweep of their second-round playoff series.
Items.vs: Montréal Canadiens vs. Winnipeg Jets

Items.description: Andrei Vasilevskiy was at his best again with the Tampa Bay Lightning in position to close out a playoff series.
Items.vs: Carolina Hurricanes vs. Tampa Bay Lightning

Items.description: Mark Stone blocked a shot on the defensive end and by the time he spun around, a pass was waiting for him with nothing but clear sailing ahead.
Items.vs: Colorado Avalanche vs. Vegas Golden Knights

Items.description: The New York Islanders got another big second period and ran past the Boston Bruins for a return trip to the Stanley Cup semifinals.
Items.vs: New York Islanders vs. Boston Bruins

Items.description: When Alex Pietrangelo signed with the Vegas Golden Knights in October, he didn’t mince words as to why he left St. Louis after 12 seasons.
Items.vs: Vegas Golden Knights vs. Colorado Avalanche

Items.description: Semyon Varlamov and the New York Islanders are on a roll.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Lightning vs. New York Islanders

Items.description: The Montreal Canadiens’ rich history didn’t mean much when it came to facing upstart Vegas Golden Knights on Monday night.
Items.vs: Vegas Golden Knights vs. Montréal Canadiens

Items.description: The Islanders stole the home ice advantage in game one. Can they take total control of the series in game two?
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Lightning vs. New York Islanders

Items.description: Vegas had a comfortable win in the first contest of the series, so the Canadiens will want to put up more of a fight in game two of the Conference Finals.
Items.vs: Vegas Golden Knights vs. Montréal Canadiens

Items.description: After keeping up his scoring touch to help Tampa Bay get a big road victory its Stanley Cup semifinal series, Brayden Point was especially proud of the Lightning's defensive effort.
Items.vs: New York Islanders vs. Tampa Bay Lightning

Items.description: The Canadiens welcome the Golden Knights to Montreal after two games in Vegas. It's a crucial contest in the series.
Items.vs: Montréal Canadiens vs. Vegas Golden Knights

Items.description: The Lightning have won back-to-back games to take a 2-1 series lead. Can the Islanders square the ledger here?
Items.vs: New York Islanders vs. Tampa Bay Lightning

Items.description: Vegas goalie Robin Lehner took a rather unconventional method in getting fired up upon being informed he was getting the start in Game 4 of the Stanley Cup semifinal series against the Montreal Canadiens.
Items.vs: Montréal Canadiens vs. Vegas Golden Knights

Items.description: There was no panic in the Tampa Bay Lightning — just another determined performance against the New York Islanders.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Lightning vs. New York Islanders

Items.description: No team has been to the Stanley Cup Final more than the Montreal Canadiens. Now they stand one victory away from a 35th appearance and their first in 28 years.
Items.vs: Vegas Golden Knights vs. Montréal Canadiens

Items.description: Trailing by two goals in the second period of an elimination game, the New York Islanders kept their composure. They got one goal before the end of the period, and tied it in the third.
Items.vs: New York Islanders vs. Tampa Bay Lightning

Items.description: Phillip Danault was patting rookie Cole Caufield on the back for playing a big role in helping the Canadiens’ remarkable playoff run, while familiar chants of `Ole, Ole’ and sounds of horn-honking could be heard from a large celebrating crowd...
Items.vs: Montréal Canadiens vs. Vegas Golden Knights

Items.description: Thanks to Andrei Vasilevskiy and another stellar defensive performance, the defending champion Tampa Bay Lightning are headed back to the Stanley Cup Final.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Lightning vs. New York Islanders

Items.description: The Stanley Cup Finals begin from Amalie Arena, as defending champions Tampa Bay take on Montreal. Who can claim game one?
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Lightning vs. Montréal Canadiens

Items.description: Nikita Kucherov starred for the Lightning in their 5-1 win over Montreal in game one. Can the Canadiens shut him down and even the series?
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Lightning vs. Montréal Canadiens

Items.description: Victor Hedman wants nothing to do with talk about how the Tampa Bay Lightning can secure their place in NHL playoff lore by becoming the second team in 22 years to repeat as Stanley Cup champions.
Items.vs: Montréal Canadiens vs. Tampa Bay Lightning

Items.description: Josh Anderson delivered in overtime, and Montreal killed Tampa Bay’s chance for a Stanley Cup sweep.
Items.vs: Montréal Canadiens vs. Tampa Bay Lightning

Items.description: Quieting the din inside Amalie Arena for just a moment, Gary Bettman looked over to the Tampa Bay Lightning and reached back into the dark days of the pandemic perhaps one last time.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Lightning vs. Montréal Canadiens
